  "notes": "North Azerbaijani (Latin-script official orthography since 1991). 9-vowel system including front unrounded /æ/ (ə) and back unrounded /ɯ/ (ı). Vowel harmony similar to Turkish. Final devoicing: b→p, c→ç, d→t, g→k. Q represents a voiced uvular stop [ɢ] in loanwords/dialects. Ğ is a fricative [ɣ] unlike Turkish where it is silent.",
